# Reusable Design and Development

## Practical 2 – Programming Fundamentals

This repository contains my practical implementation for **Unit 1** of the Reusable Design and Development module.

## 📘 Unit Overview

This unit focuses on:

* Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
* Introduction to Software Design Patterns
* Understanding reusable and extensible code structures

## 🎯 Learning Outcomes

After completing this unit, I am able to:

* Discuss object-oriented design patterns and their principles
* Identify business cases where design patterns provide best-practice solutions
* Apply the Strategy Design Pattern in a practical implementation

## 🧠 Practical Implemented

### Strategy Design Pattern

The Strategy Pattern was implemented to demonstrate how a system can dynamically change behavior at runtime by encapsulating algorithms into separate classes.

## 💡 Key Concepts Demonstrated

* Encapsulation
* Polymorphism
* Abstraction
* Open/Closed Principle
* Separation of concerns

